                        <interp inst="t18580405-name-746" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM WEBSTER</persName>
                  </hi>. This florin and shilling are both, counterfeit.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> Does it stand to, reason that I would take a had shilling to the station to get myself into trouble?</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">The Prisoner called</hi>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18580405-name-747" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18580405-name-747" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18580405-name-747" type="surname" value="SWEENEY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18580405-name-747" type="given" value="MARY ANN"></interp>MARY ANN SWEENEY</persName>
                  </hi>. I went with the prisoner twice to the coffee house in Suffolk Street; first at half past 12 o'clock at night, and again between 3 and 4 o'clock—he asked me what I would have; I said, "A cup of tea and a slice of bread and butter," and he called for a cup of coffee—he asked her whether she had a room; she said, "Yes"—he asked the price, and she said 1<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.—heoffered 1<hi rend="italic">s</hi>., and she said, "As we are not busy, you shall have it for 1<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.;" she tried the shilling twice before putting it into her pocket, and then went into the kitchen to get a candle—I said that I would not go up stairs till I had had a cup of tea, and he said then be would not stop at all—he asked for his money back; she turned to a person in the kitchen, and said, "Shall I give it to him back?"—she said, "Do not have any dispute about it,"when she gave it to him, he said, "This is a bad shilling"—she said, "It is the one you gave me"—he said, "No; I gave you a new, Victoria shilling"—shesaid that she had no other—only one young chap was present, sitting at the bar—I had no refreshment at all—two men called for something when we went in first, and gave her a 2<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. piece.</p>
